Excellent movie!!  We were very pleased we bought this one.  The professor, played by Kevin Sorbo, who wanted his entire class to sign a paper that God was dead,  believed he could then 'get on with the class'.  But one young man just couldn't sign his name to something he believed was not true, really got the professor irate.  And enough that he gives the young man a week to prove that God was real.  We find out behind the scenes the lifestyle of the professor and you end up feeling very sorry for his wife.  Then you find out why he is so bitter towards God.  This movie has a very surprising ending which we did not expect at all!  Very good movie and we would recommend to all, but might be a little too deep for young ones.  Excellent for 7th graders on up.
